The paper focuses on the security risks of voice-controlled third-party skills on Amazon Alexa and Google Home, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The study also involves user studies and real-world deployments, which could be categorized under human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and social and information networks (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of automatic detection techniques, which could be classified under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and cryptography and security (cs.CY).
